replies.body:
I mean if you're in bronze or silver elo and you don't mind being flamed, Dr Mundo support is basically just doctor mundo toplane back from S1 and 2 but with a little less gold and tankiness. You do so much damage and if you get ahead during the midgame, then you don't even need to bother with peeling since you'll just run at the enemy carry and sup and 1v2 them no sweat. My platinum friend did it to troll in a few games with me and then I tried it and even though I still prefer traditional supports as the support main I am, it's still incredibly strong and can carry so hard even if your adc is a potato. Your midgame powerspikes as Dr.Mundo Support involve doing as much damage as a full ap support and being constant annoying poke in lane, thanks to almost free spammable %hp cleavers and yet being as tanky as an alistair or braum. You can towerdive like the best of tank supports with your ult letting you stay under tower for basically as long as you please, you're a decently strong duelist with alot more damage threat than most other tank supports, you really aren't easy to kill if you get caught out, your new e pushes towers so quickly and your poke and lane sustain basically outperforms every other champion in the game.

Try carrying a few normal games with Dr.Mundo Support before taking it to ranked though and try to buy 'team benefit' items where you can since you do sacrifice alot of peel when going mundo sup and whilst mundo sup can 1v1 a toplaner or jungle if you can keep up in gold, lategame you'll need these items to compensate for the lack of cc, peel and survivability you would have offered to your squishies with other picks..

